Position: The position of the point attractor from the source of the emitter.
Range: The radial range of the attractor.
Strength: The strength of the point attractor.
StrengthByDistance: The strength curve is a function of distance or of time.
bAffectBaseVelocity: If true, the velocity adjustment will be applied to the base velocity.
bUseWorldSpacePosition: If true, treat the position as world space.  So don't transform the the point to localspace.
Positive_X: Whether particles can move along the positive X axis.
Positive_Y: Whether particles can move along the positive Y axis.
Positive_Z: Whether particles can move along the positive Z axis.
Negative_X: Whether particles can move along the negative X axis.
Negative_Y: Whether particles can move along the negative Y axis.
Negative_Z: Whether particles can move along the negative Z axis.
